'''Robert Lee Brewer''' (born March 1, 1939 in [[Alhambra, California]]) was an [[United States|American]] [[figure skater]]. He won the bronze medal at the [[U.S. Figure Skating Championships]] in 1959 and 1960. He placed 7th at the [[1960 Winter Olympics]].
After retiring from skating, Brewer became a pilot and a doctor.
